CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 16, 1966, pg. 1B reads:"Young Set Have Fun Too At Alpha Dance - Between Sets - The Student Union of the University of Pittsburgh was the scene of youthful gaiety when Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity sponsored a benefit dance for the United Negro College Fund. It was under the supervision of the UNCF's Women's Division, headed by Miss Nancy Lee....Happy Twosome - Among the members of the smart young set enjoying the festivities at the dance sponsored by the undergraduate chapter of Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity recently, wre Harry K. Parker and Evelyn Savido.  Held at the University of Pittsburgh Student Union, proceeds benefited the United Negro College Fund."
TitMainTitle: Harry K. Parker and Evelyn Savjdo seated on bench as base of staircase in University of Pittsburgh Student Union for Alpha Phi Alpha benefit dance for United Negro College Fund
